message:
...High Wind Warning in effect until 7 am EST Tuesday...

The National Weather Service in Morristown has issued a High Wind
Warning...which is in effect until 7 am EST Tuesday. The Wind
Advisory is no longer in effect. 

* Event...southerly winds increasing to 20 to 40 mph with gusts up
 to 60 mph

* timing...strong southerly winds tonight and continuing until
 around daybreak Tuesday.

* Impacts...the windy conditions may down trees and power lines. 
 Loose outdoor objects should be secured. Motorists should be 
 extra cautious to cross wind especially when driving in the 
 higher elevations and/or driving high profiles vehicles. 

Precautionary/preparedness actions...

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph and/or
gusts of 58 mph or stronger can be expected at times. Winds of
these magnitudes can cause property damage and power outages. 
Motorists should use caution...especially those in high profile
vehicles.
